\sin(\pi/3) = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\sin^2(x) + \cos^2(x) = 1
 \cos^2(\pi/3) = 1 - \left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\right)^2 = 1 - \frac{3}{4} = \frac{1}{4}. 
